S|# YVON OS — Master Build Plan|> **Rule:** Each phase has a plan doc → user approves → execute → verify → next phase. // > No code changes happen without prior ap. // ---
S|Phase 0: Responsive Overhaul (FOUNDATION)|**Why first:** The entire UI is desktop-only (sidebar fixed 248px, no mobile toggle, grid layouts break below 1024px). Everything else depends on this being solid. // ### What changes: // \| Component \| Desktop (now) \| Tablet (768-1023px) \| Mobile (<768px) \| // \|-----------\|:---:\|:---:\|:---:\| // \| **Sidebar** \| Fixed 248px, always visible \| Collapsible to 64px (icons only), expand on hover \| Hidden, hamburger slide-over from left \| // \| **TopBar** \| Full search + breadcrumb + age
S|Phase 1: Venture/Wiring Setup|Wire Novizio + Hourbour into the workspace system. Currently workspaces are demo data (Canela, Valhalla, By Design, Vibe with AI). // ### What changes: // - Map workspace `vibe` → Novizio (fashion e-commerce) // - Map workspace `bydesign` → Hourbour (fintech SaaS) // - Wire `WorkspaceContext` to read from `lib/vtr-ctx.ts` // - Connect `WorkspaceSwitcher` to real Supabase ventures table // - Verify vtr-scoped data loading across all pages // - Remove demo workspaces (Canela, Valhalla → keep as fu
S|Phase 2: Decision Queue|The #1 page. Connect Marcus filter → real agt output → 7 actionable items. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Marcus reads actual agt sessions/tasks/PRs from Supabase // - Backend: Filter layer (Marcus decides: auto-handle vs escalate) // - Frontend: Wire live data into dec cards (not hardcoded) // - Frontend: Defer/snooze with real Supabase persistence // - Integration: Telegram nudge via `send_message` when decisions pile up // - Wire: Clear-my-queue one-by-one mode // - Wire: Workspace filter
S|Phase 3: Task Board|agt task proposal → ap → execute → rv pl. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Task proposal endpoint (agents submit JSON proposals) // - Backend: Marcus auto-ap learning (3 same-type → auto) // - Frontend: Real Kanban data from Supabase (not demo cards) // - Frontend: Live Activity tracker (read from agt sessions) // - Frontend: rv → escalate to dec Queue // - Wire: Learning system (which tasks get auto-ap) // **Effort:** ~5-6 hours   // **Files touched:** ~12 // ---
S|Phase 4: Social Approvals + Scheduler|Instagram cnt ap + cross-platform scheduling. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Wire Leonardo → Creative Studio image generation // - Backend: William A/B copy generation via Hermes spawn // - Frontend: Real image grid from Supabase storage // - Frontend: A/B copy variants (real, not demo) // - Frontend: Drag-drop scheduler with real posting slots // - Backend: Scheduled post execution via cron // - Wire: Failure triage (retry failed posts) // **Effort:** ~4-5 hours   // **Files touched:** ~15 
S|Phase 5: Advisory Council + War Room|5-agt debate system with live War Room. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Council agt orchestration (spawn 5 Hermes agents in parallel) // - Backend: Debate synthesis → recommendation cards // - Backend: Pattern tracker (recurring themes across debates) // - Frontend: Real recommendations (not hardcoded) // - Frontend: War Room live chat (WebSocket or SSE streaming) // - Frontend: Topic scheduling ("set today's topic") // - Wire: Accept → create task → assign agt workflow // **Effort:** ~6-8 ho
S|Phase 6: Software Pipeline|PR-only gate + QA + rv pl. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Dev agt creates PR, never pushes to main // - Backend: Quinn QA gate (react-doctor, lint, typecheck, test) // - Frontend: Portfolio view with real GitHub repos // - Frontend: Kanban with real tasks from GitHub issues/PRs // - Wire: QA fail → back to Planning // - Wire: QA pass → escalate to dec Queue (CEO merge) // **Effort:** ~4-5 hours   // **Files touched:** ~10 // ---
S|Phase 7: Brain & Wiki|3D knw graph + library browser. // ### What changes: // - Wire: Real Supabase vector data → graph nodes // - Wire: Library tab → browse agt-created MD files // - Wire: Visibility scoping (Private/Team/vtr/Cross-vtr) // - Wire: "What agents don't know" gaps panel // - Frontend: 3D graph improvements (performance, touch) // **Effort:** ~3-4 hours   // **Files touched:** ~8 // ---
S|Phase 8: Content Pipeline + YouTube Studio|cnt creation workflow. // ### What changes: // - Backend: cnt intelligence engine → real ideas // - Backend: Kai's Read → cnt recommendations // - Frontend: Real Kanban data (ideas → published) // - Wire: Cadence tracking (on/off schedule) // **Effort:** ~3-4 hours   // **Files touched:** ~10 // ---
S|Phase 9: Email Inbox|4-account email with inline replies. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Email provider integration (Resend SDK already in deps) // - Backend: Auto-draft responses (Hermes agt reads + drafts) // - Frontend: Inline reply composer (real, not demo) // - Frontend: Triage mode with real emails // - Wire: "What we know about sender" from Supabase mem // **Effort:** ~5-6 hours   // **Files touched:** ~10 // ---
S|Phase 10: Newsletter|Kit API nl studio. // ### What changes: // - Backend: Kit API integration (audience, compose, send, anl) // - Frontend: Real subscriber data, real compose/send // - Wire: ap gate (draft → rv → send) // **Effort:** ~3-4 hours   // **Files touched:** ~8 // ---
S|Phase 11: Remaining Pages|One-by-one wiring for lower-priority pages: // - Asset Lab (Leonardo gallery) // - Trend Radar (Isaac) // - Idea Feed // - prd Calendar // - Shorts pl + Shorts // - YouTube anl + soc anl // - Skill Workshop // - Hardware & Runtime // - People, Docs, Logs, Projects // **Effort:** ~8-10 hours total (spread across sub-phases) // ---
S|Phase 12: Analytics Integration|Real-time metrics across all dashboards. // ### What changes: // - Wire Supabase anl tables to all dashboard KPIs // - Token usage → real data on Operations // - cp metrics → real data on cp dashboard // - Revenue metrics → real data on Consulting CRM // **Effort:** ~4-5 hours   // **Files touched:** ~15 // ---
S|Phase 13: Testing & QA|Comprehensive test suite. // ### What changes: // - Unit tests for lib modules // - Integration tests for API routes // - E2E tests for critical flows (dec Queue, Task Board, Software pl) // - Quinn QA automation in CI // **Effort:** ~6-8 hours // ---
S|Phase 14: Production Hardening|Performance, sec, monitoring. // ### What changes: // - Rate limiting on all API routes // - Error boundary components // - Loading skeletons for all data-dependent pages // - Performance optimization (bundle size, image optimization) // - sec audit (API key handling, RLS, CSP) // **Effort:** ~4-5 hours // ---
